<h2>FAQ</h2>

<h3>What is Mettle?</h3>

<p>Mettle is a tool for testing big data sets in data integration and other database-heavy applications.</p>

<p>We believe that that good testing tools will remove a significant barrier to entry for DI teams' Agile adoption.  However, it is a very complex problem to solve and a traditional TDD-style framework will not cut it (if it were that easy, everyone would be doing it by now).</p>

<p>The right tool for the job will be...</p>

<ul>
  <li>Technology agnostic - able to interface with a variety of databases, platforms and ETL tools</li>
  <li>Quick and easy to get started with</li>
  <li>Simple for business people and analysts to understand - tests should be easy to create and results easy access and understand</li>
  <li>Powerful enough for developers to do complex things</li>
  <li>Probably using web technologies (even if they are hosted within an enterprise)</li>
</ul>

